OL,3,C'We will be forever grateful':
OL,4,CMargaret Le Cras' SS Vega memories 80
OL,5,Cyears on
OL,7,FShe recalls: "(My parents)
OL,8,Fdeliberately didn't speak to me in
OL,9,FEnglish, not that they didn't speak to
OL,10,Feach other sometimes but patois or the
OL,11,FGuernesiais, that was the language
OL,12,Fthey used.
OL,14,F"I think it was so that if I knew
OL,15,Fthey'd hidden food away and the
OL,16,FGermans came and asked where it was I
OL,17,Fwouldn't have been able to tell them.
OL,19,F"I wouldn't have understood and they
OL,20,Fwouldn't understand me."
