OL,3,C'We will be forever grateful':
OL,4,CMargaret Le Cras' SS Vega memories 80
OL,5,Cyears on
OL,7,FMargaret may not have been able to
OL,8,Ftalk to the Germans but growing up,
OL,9,Fshe understood who was in charge.
OL,11,FShe remembers the first time the
OL,12,FGermans stole from her family, saying:
OL,13,F"My father had grown onions in the
OL,14,Fgarden, now the Germans saw the onions
OL,15,Fand knew he'd harvested them.
OL,17,F"One day they came to inspect the
OL,18,Fhouse and I saw the Germans going up
OL,19,Finto what was the attic and coming
OL,20,Fback with, obviously, our onions and I
OL,21,Fwas very aware of that.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/10
