OL,3,C'We will be forever grateful':
OL,4,CMargaret Le Cras' SS Vega memories 80
OL,5,Cyears on
OL,7,F"There were some little pinecones near
OL,8,FSt Saviour's Church and if I saw any,
OL,9,FI would gather them to collect and
OL,10,Ftake to school because when the
OL,11,Fweather was cold, (my teacher) would
OL,12,Flight a stove for heat."
OL,14,FChristmas lunch in 1944 was a meagre
OL,15,Faffair and only the arrival of the Red
OL,16,FCross ship a few days after, kept
OL,17,Fthousands alive.
OL,19,FWhat did the Red Cross parcels contain?
OL,21,FThe Canadian parcels contained:
